Body: A package had eighteen cookies in it. After eating some there were nine left.

Question: How many were eaten?
Question_trans: 얼마나 많이 먹었습니까?

Body: Faye and her mom were picking carrots from their garden. Faye picked 23 and her mother picked 5. If only 12 of the carrots were good,

Question: how many bad carrots did they have?
Question_trans: 나쁜 당근이 몇 개나 있었나요?

Body: In the first half of a trivia game Kaleb scored forty-three points. In the second half he scored twenty-three points.

Question: How many points did he score total?
Question_trans: 그는 총 몇 점을 득점했습니까?

Body: Chris has 18 soccer cards. His friend, Charlie, has 32 cards.

Question: How many fewer cards does Chris have?

Body: Shelby had 92 pieces of candy. She gave 4 pieces each to 9 friends.

Question_trans: 쉘비는 사탕 몇 조각을 남겼습니까?

Body: An architect built a house with ten bedrooms total. If the second floor had two bedrooms.

Body: The giant Ferris wheel can seat 56 people. There are 92 people waiting in line.

Question_trans: 이번에는 안 타는 사람이 몇이나 될까?

Body: Winter is almost here and most animals are migrating to warmer countries. There are 67 bird families living near the mountain. If 32 bird families flew away for winter,
Body_trans: 겨울이 거의 다가오고 있으며 대부분의 동물이 따뜻한 나라로 이주하고 있습니다. 산 근처에는 67개의 새 가족이 살고 있습니다. 32가구의 새들이 겨울을 나기 위해 날아갔다면,
Question: how many bird families were left near the mountain?
Question_trans: 산 근처에 얼마나 많은 새 가족이 남아 있었습니까?

Body: A company was offering a special on cell phones for $2 each. But only if you spent 7 dollars a month for 4 months.
Body_trans: 한 회사가 휴대폰에 각각 2달러에 특별 상품을 제공하고 있었습니다. 단, 4개월 동안 한 달에 7달러를 지출한 경우에만 가능합니다.
Question: How much would it end up costing you total if you bought 1 phone?

Body: Rob also compared the Empire State Building and the Petronas Towers.

Body: Upon finishing the treehouse, Charlie's mother served them freshly baked cookies. If Charlie ate 15 cookies, his father ate 10 and his mother only ate 5,
Body_trans: 나무 위의 집을 완성하자 찰리의 어머니는 갓 구운 쿠키를 그들에게 제공했습니다. 찰리가 쿠키 15개를 먹었다면 그의 아버지는 10개를, 그의 어머니는 5개만 먹었다면,
Question: how many cookies were eaten in total?
Question_trans: 총 몇 개의 쿠키를 먹었습니까?

Body: Mike owned sixty-four baseball cards. For his birthday he got eighteen more.

Question: How many cards does Mike have total?

Body: The roller coaster at the state fair costs 6 tickets per ride. If 8 friends were going to ride the roller coaster,

Question: how many tickets would they need?

Body: 172 students are forming teams for a mountaineering competition. Each team should have 18 students.

Question: How many teams can they form?
Question_trans: 얼마나 많은 팀을 구성할 수 있습니까?

Body: Andy had 31 baseball cards. His dad gave him some more. Then Andy had 50 baseball cards.
Body_trans: Andy는 31장의 야구 카드를 가지고 있었습니다. 그의 아버지는 그에게 더 많은 것을 주었다. 그리고 Andy는 50장의 야구 카드를 가지고 있었습니다.
Question: How many baseball cards did Andy get from his dad?
Question_trans: Andy는 아버지로부터 몇 장의 야구 카드를 받았습니까?

Body: Bryan took a look at his books as well. If he has 56 books in each of his 9 bookshelves,

Question: how many books does he have in total?

Body: Paul was reading through his favorite book series. Each week he read four different books.
Body_trans: Paul은 그가 가장 좋아하는 책 시리즈를 읽고 있었습니다. 그는 매주 4권의 다른 책을 읽었습니다.

Body: While organizing her files, Bianca deleted 2 pictures, 8 songs and 7 text files.

Body: Debby was placing her spare change into stacks. One stack had 4 coins and the other had 8.

Body: A furniture store had fifteen chairs. After selling some, there was three left.
